  <bioghist id="aspace_74f261f79faa8e5faed607b129812c6f">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Consular official and business executive.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_d6e5d314db8772013a5fd021fb3885d4">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Included are a letterbook, a scrapbook, and a few loose papers. Most of the letters are to business associates and are primarily concerned with Shaw's unsuccessful efforts to raise funds in England to build an electric railroad in Canada and with the founding of the Canadian Niagara Power Company, of which Shaw was president. The scrapbook consists of newspaper clippings and assorted memorabilia concerning Shaw's service as U.S. consul in Toronto.</p>  </scopecontent>
